This move, according to the gameknot database, isn't the best option. 54.6% score for black.. pretty darn good. The idea is to get the knight to f5, but if one move is played incorrectly, the game is lost for white. The position is too sharp for any errors!
Usually black plays 16.. b3, but this move is also good, certainly better against me! - moving in his knight for the attack.

A stunning elegant move that caught me offguard! If I capture with axb3, the opening of the a-file with check leads to my downfall.

Much more subtly, after 24. cxb3 axb3 I am in some trouble.. 
For example, 25. a3 loses promptly to 25.. Nb5 26. Qc1 Rc8 where I can't stop the deadly threat of Nxa3.
25. Nb4 d5 is crushing as well.
